model_explanation: "Sam only gave SUE grapes" means Sue is the only person to whom Sam gave grapes, and it says nothing about giving grapes to Tom. Therefore, S2 is independent of S1.
"Sam only gave ELLEN bananas" means Ellen is the only person Sam gave bananas to. If Sam also gave Mary bananas, that contradicts the statement.
"Sam only gave ROB bananas" means Rob is the only person Sam gave bananas to, but it says nothing about whether or not Sam gave Rob oranges. Therefore, S2 is independent of S1.
"Sam only gave MARY bananas" means that bananas were the only thing Sam gave to Mary. If Sam also gave her apples, that contradicts the statement.
"Sam only gave SUE ORANGES" means that Sue is the only person who received oranges, so it follows that Rob did not receive oranges. Thus, S2 is entailed by S1.
"Sam only gave BILL grapes" means that Bill is the only person who received grapes. If Sam also gave Sue grapes, that contradicts the statement.
"Sam only gave SUE oranges" means Sue is the only person who received oranges. If Sam also gave Rob oranges, that contradicts the statement.
